SITUATION ANALYSIS AND NEEDS

   The violent conflict in Syria has been escalating in intensity and
   complexity since March 2011 with devastating humanitarian consequences.
   Recent estimates suggest over 100,000 have been killed[18][1], 5.1m
   Syrians are internally displaced[19][2] and 2.4m registered refugees in
   neighbouring countries[20][3]. In July 2013 alone, UN DSS recorded
   3,414 incidents of armed clashes and heavy weapons use in Syria (see
   map below). The extensive use of indiscriminate, area-wide weapons is a
   serious threat to Protection of Civilians, causing both immediate and
   long-lasting damage. These weapons result in Explosive Remnants of War
   such as rockets, cluster munitions and IEDs, endangering the lives and
   livelihoods of generations of Syrians if a rapid and concerted
   clearance effort is not undertaken in the immediate cessation of
   conflict.
